com.github.maxstupo.flatengine.map.tile

Class Tileset

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.maxstupo.flatengine.map.tile.Tileset

  • public class Tileset
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a tileset, it will split a given tileset image into tiles that can be obtained via getTileByGid(int) or getTileByLocalId(int).
    Author:
    Maxstupo

    • Constructor Detail

      • Tileset

        public Tileset(int firstGid,
               java.lang.String name,
               int tileWidth,
               int tileHeight,
               int tileSpacing,
               int tileMargin,
               java.awt.image.BufferedImage tilesetImage,
               java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,MapProperties> tileProperties,
               java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<MapObject>> tileCollisions)
        Create a new Tileset object.
        Parameters:
        firstGid - the first global id of the first tile within this tileset.
        name - the name of this tileset.
        tileWidth - the width in pixels for each tile.
        tileHeight - the height in pixels for each tile.
        tileSpacing - the spacing of each tile in pixels.
        tileMargin - the margin of the tileset in pixels.
        tilesetImage - the tileset image.
        tileProperties - properties for each tile, set to null to ignore. Note: The array length can be less than the total tiles within the tileset.
        tileCollisions - map objects representing collision areas of the given tile id.
